<cell id="cell-0"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type># Lab 3.4 — RAG failure modes
Walk 12 canned transcripts. Tag each with one of:
boundary_split, coverage_gap, redundancy, numeric_exact.
No LLM calls. ~$0.00.</cell id="cell-0">
<cell id="cell-1">import json
from pathlib import Path
cases = json.loads(Path("data/transcripts.json").read_text())
for i, c in enumerate(cases):
    print(f"[{i}] {c['query']}")
    for r in c["top_k"]:
        print(f"    ({r['doc_id']}) {r['text'][:70]}")
    print(f"    YOUR TAG:  ___")
    print(f"    ANSWER:    {c['failure_mode']}")
    print()</cell id="cell-1">
<cell id="cell-2"># Verify taxonomy coverage
TAXONOMY = {"boundary_split","coverage_gap","redundancy","numeric_exact"}
covered = {c["failure_mode"] for c in cases} & TAXONOMY
print(f"covered: {sorted(covered)}  score={len(covered)}/4")</cell id="cell-2">
<cell id="cell-3"># Bonus: reproduce the boundary-split failure on real embeddings
import numpy as np, os, voyageai
vo = voyageai.Client()
text = "Hyperparameters\nlearning_rate: 3e-4\nbatch_size: 256\nwarmup_steps: 2000\n" + ("noise " * 40) + "Training used AdamW with cosine decay."
chunks = [text[i:i+80] for i in range(0, len(text), 80)]
E = np.array(vo.embed(chunks, model="voyage-3", input_type="document").embeddings)
E /= np.linalg.norm(E, axis=1, keepdims=True)
q = np.array(vo.embed(["what is the learning rate"], model="voyage-3", input_type="query").embeddings[0])
q /= np.linalg.norm(q)
top = (E @ q).argsort()[-3:][::-1]
for i in top: print(f"score={E[i] @ q:.3f} chunk={chunks[i][:70]!r}")
# Observation: the heading chunk and the value chunk are never both in the top-3.</cell id="cell-3">